He received his bachelor's degree from the University of Pennsylvania in 1956 and a Master's Degree from Harvard University in 1958.

Hansell taught music history and harpsichord at University of California, Davis before joining the faculty of the University of Iowa in 1973.
He retired from the University of Iowa in 1999 as Professor Emeritus of Musicology.
